news.title: Pay rent for using municipal property or face action: Canacona civic body
news.para: Some councillors at the council meeting said the houses built illegally before 2018 should be regularised by giving house numbers, which they said will add revenue to the council.

news.title: Coimbatore: Vellalore to get construction and demolition waste recycling plant
news.para: The state government has given its approval for the plant. While the Chennai corporation already has the facility, the state government has given its approval to establish the plants in Coimbatore and Madurai.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet's nod for acquiring land for phase 3 & 4 of Noida airport
news.para: By 2070, the airport will have six runways and four terminal buildings with a capacity to cater to 225 million passengers annually and handle 10 million tonne of cargo.

news.title: Nashik: NMSCDCL's greenfield township plan in Makhmalabad hits roadblock
news.para: The agency had plans to acquire around 750 acres of land from the farmers to create basic infrastructure like roads, drainage lines etc but the farmers are refusing to give up their land.

news.title: Lucknow development body to cancel allotment if arrears not paid in a week
news.para: In a review meeting, LDA vice chairperson Indramani Tripathi gave instructions for the recovery from defaulters who have been allotted residential and commercial properties.

news.title: Thane civic body earns Rs 500 crore in property tax, Majiwada tops with Rs 174 crore
news.para: As per data accessed till November 23, the developing areas of Ghodbunder Road generated Rs 173.9 crore of the total Rs 502 crore collected since the start of the fiscal.

news.title: Over 18,000 houses get nod for Uttarakhand under PMAY-Gramin
news.para: "We are making the required efforts to take the benefits of development to the people standing in the far flung and remote areas of Uttarakhand," CM Dhami said.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body gets 1,088 applications for regularization of construction
news.para: Owners of properties who wish to regularize their illegal construction are to apply through the E-Nagar portal, said a press release issued on Friday.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Multi-storey flats on single-unit plots to be razed in Vasundhara
news.para: The order has come from the Housing Board’s deputy commissioner in the wake of multiple complaints to the commissioner over rampant illegal construction in the township.

news.title: Assam REAT directs Arya Erectors India to deposit Rs 32 lakh to consider plea
news.para: The appeal was filed by M/s Arya Erectors India Pvt. Ltd. against an order dated 21.09.2022 passed by the RERA, Assam wherein it had directed the builder to pay the buyer of a villa interest on Rs. 1.5 Crore with effect from 28/08/2020 until the handing over of possession of the villa.

news.title: Delhi HC grants bail to former MD & CEO of YES Bank in money laundering case
news.para: The case pertains to ED's probe against Gautam Thapar, Avantha Realty, Oyster Buildwell, and several others alleging criminal breach of trust, cheating, criminal conspiracy, and forgery for diversion or misappropriation of public money during the 2017 to 2019 period.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal structures in Aravalis to be razed next week
news.para: NGT in August 2020 ordered an end to the illegal tree felling, construction activities and to restore the forest in Sonya Ghosh case. The plan is to demolish 200 illegal constructions in Aravalis in 15 days.

news.title: Seren Infrastructure caught stealing electricity worth Rs 33 lakh in Thane
news.para: The MSEDCL found that the construction company — Seren Infrastructure — has been stealing electricity with the help of a remote facility.

news.title: Maharashtra: ED case against 65 builders booked for cheating buyers
news.para: The developers, mostly local, illegally constructed buildings, prepared fake documents of permissions, used them to obtain Rera certificates and sold the flats.

news.title: China Evergrande Group communicates with Wuhan over repossessed land
news.para: The Jiangxia District government in the central city of Wuhan retrieved its land-use rights over the undeveloped sites at the developer's Evergrande Technology Tourism City project on Nov. 16.
